## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="742cc-102">由 <xref:System.Globalization.CalendarWeekRule> 属性返回并由区域性的当前日历用来确定日历周规则的 <xref:System.Globalization.DateTimeFormatInfo.CalendarWeekRule%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> 枚举的成员。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="742cc-102">A member of the <xref:System.Globalization.CalendarWeekRule> enumeration is returned by the <xref:System.Globalization.DateTimeFormatInfo.CalendarWeekRule%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> property and is used by the culture's current calendar to determine the calendar week rule.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="742cc-103">枚举值还用作 <xref:System.Globalization.Calendar.GetWeekOfYear%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> 方法的参数。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="742cc-103">The enumeration value is also used as a parameter to the <xref:System.Globalization.Calendar.GetWeekOfYear%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="742cc-104">日历周规则取决于表示一周的第一天的 <xref:System.DayOfWeek?displayProperty=nameWithType> 值以及 <xref:System.Globalization.CalendarWeekRule> 值。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="742cc-104">Calendar week rules depend on the <xref:System.DayOfWeek?displayProperty=nameWithType> value that indicates the first day of the week in addition to depending on a <xref:System.Globalization.CalendarWeekRule> value.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="742cc-105"><xref:System.Globalization.DateTimeFormatInfo.FirstDayOfWeek%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType>属性的默认值为提供一个区域性，但任何<xref:System.DayOfWeek>值可以指定为一周中的第一天<xref:System.Globalization.Calendar.GetWeekOfYear%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType>方法。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="742cc-105">The <xref:System.Globalization.DateTimeFormatInfo.FirstDayOfWeek%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> property provides the default value for a culture, but any <xref:System.DayOfWeek> value can be specified as the first day of the week in the <xref:System.Globalization.Calendar.GetWeekOfYear%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="742cc-106">基于 FirstDay 值的第一周可以有 1 到 7 天。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="742cc-106">The first week based on the FirstDay value can have one to seven days.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="742cc-107">始终基于 FirstFullWeek 值的第一周为七天。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="742cc-107">The first week based on the FirstFullWeek value always has seven days.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="742cc-108">基于 FirstFourDayWeek 值的第一周可以有四到七天。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="742cc-108">The first week based on the FirstFourDayWeek value can have four to seven days.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="742cc-109">例如，在公历日历中，假设年 (1 月 1 日) 的第一天落在特定的星期二和一周中的指定的第一天是星期日。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="742cc-109">For example, in the Gregorian calendar, suppose that the first day of the year (January 1) falls on a Tuesday and the designated first day of the week is Sunday.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="742cc-110">选择 FirstFullWeek 定义为每年的第一周的开始，第一个星期日 (1 月 6 日)。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="742cc-110">Selecting FirstFullWeek defines the first Sunday (January 6) as the beginning of the first week of the year.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="742cc-111">每年的第一个五天被视为去年的最后一周的一部分。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="742cc-111">The first five days of the year are considered part of the last week of the previous year.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="742cc-112">与此相反，选择 FirstFourDayWeek 定义年 (1 月 1 日) 的第一天为开始，在一年的第一周因为有多个四天从 1 月 1 日到以下前一天星期日。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="742cc-112">In contrast, selecting FirstFourDayWeek defines the first day of the year (January 1) as the beginning of the first week of the year because there are more than four days from January 1 to the day before the following Sunday.</span></span>  
  
